CAUTIONARY STATEMENT CONCERNING FORWARD-LOOKING STATEMENTS

IN THIS ANNUAL REPORT ON FORM 10-K WE

HAVE MADE FORWARD-LOOKING STATEMENTS. THESE STATEMENTS ARE BASED ON OUR ESTIMATES AND ASSUMPTIONS AND ARE SUBJECT TO RISKS AND UNCERTAINTIES. FORWARD-LOOKING STATEMENTS INCLUDE INFORMATION CONCERNING OUR POSSIBLE OR ASSUMED FUTURE RESULTS OF

OPERATIONS. FORWARD-LOOKING STATEMENTS ALSO INCLUDE THOSE PRECEDED OR FOLLOWED BY THE WORDS ANTICIPATES, BELIEVES, ESTIMATES, HOPES OR SIMILAR EXPRESSIONS. FOR THOSE STATEMENTS, WE CLAIM THE PROTECTION

OF THE SAFE HARBOR FOR FORWARD-LOOKING STATEMENTS CONTAINED IN THE PRIVATE SECURITIES LITIGATION REFORM ACT OF 1995.

THE

FOLLOWING IMPORTANT FACTORS, ALONG WITH THOSE DISCUSSED ELSEWHERE IN THIS ANNUAL REPORT, COULD AFFECT FUTURE RESULTS AND COULD CAUSE THOSE RESULTS TO DIFFER MATERIALLY FROM THOSE EXPRESSED IN THE FORWARD-LOOKING STATEMENTS.



THE EFFECTS OF ADVERSE CONDITIONS IN THE U.S. AND INTERNATIONAL ECONOMIES;



THE EFFECTS OF COMPETITION IN OUR MARKETS;

